idinfo.native: Microsoft Windows XP Version 5.1 (Build 2600) Service Pack 3; ESRI ArcCatalog 9.3.0.1770

descript.abstract: CMAP Subzones are units of geography that are used in the land use and transportation modeling activities of CMAP. Subzones are mostly derived from quarter sections, unless the subzone falls outside the CMAP planning area. This latest edition of the subzones (Subzone09) only contains one significant difference with the 2007 subzones (Subzone07). The subzones in Kendall County and Aux Sable Township (Grundy County) now are the size of quarter sections, just like the subzones in the 6 counties. Subzone09 now is comprised of 16819 subzones, up from 15401 in Subzone07.
descript.purpose: To provide a smaller land use and transportation modeling geography for Kendall County and Aux Sable Township in Grundy County.
